title: UCLA freshman QB Josh set school record for most completions in a game
text:
UCLA freshman QB Josh set school record for most completions in a game 
UCLA QB Josh Rosen looked unbelievable vs. Cal. Gary A. Vasquez-USA TODAY Sports Oct 23, 2015 at 12:27a ET 0Shares 
UCLA fans may have been worried about starting a true freshman when the season started, but Josh Rosen continues to improve every game. true Josh Rosen just set the UCLA record for completions in a game. Which is equal parts bad Cal defense and having no RB’s tonight. — Bryan Fischer (@BryanDFischer) October 23, 2015 
Earlier in the game , UCLA's kicker set a school record for longest field goal completed. Rosen joined the record breakers club when he connected for his 34th completion -- which became the new UCLA record for most completions in a game. Rosen ended the game with 34 completions, 399 yards and 3 TD's. 
OC Register's Joey Kaufman notes that Green Bay Packers quarterback and former UCLA star Brett Hundley recorded 33 completions vs. Memphis last season. MORE NEWS: Want stories delivered to you? Sign up for our College Football newsletters. 0
